<Author>LaurenA1
<Content>Perfect for practical travellers My boyfriend and I stayed for two nights during July and found the hotel to be pretty much as its shown on the website - whihc is a good thing. The room was a decent size, fairly basic in that it consisted of a bed, desk and chair, but then that is exactly what we expected. The decor - all red, white and black gives a clean, modern atmosphere. There is also a safe in each room and loads of power points - handly for computers/ipods/phones etc. The staff we encountered could not be described as super-friendly but were certainly polite and attentive.The location is great - the northern part of El Raval so on a narrow street packed with funky music and clothes shops as well as some cheaper cafes and bars, but also less than 5 mins walk to Las Ramblas and into the Gothic Quarter or north into the rest of the city.I did notice a few things that didn't really bother us in the end but would certainly bother others:- the AC seemed to have two settings - Arctic or off;- the corridors smell very strongly of cigarette smoke (although our room was fine);- there was some street noise in our room on the second floor - people during the night and traffic (seemed to be a lot of trucks loading and unloading) during the day so earplugs are recommended if you're a light sleeper; and- the lifts take an age to arrive so we usually took the stairs.But overall I'd recommend this to travellers, especially younger travellers who like somewhere more upmarket than the hostels who might appreciate the modernity and basic aesthetic of the place. 
