<Author>SmrOrng
<Content>Recommend Ciutat Vella This hotel appears to have only been open a month, but I found the room very comfortable and most of the services as advertised. I paid 120 Euros a night for 4 nights (internet special), and bought a Aerobus ticket for less than 4 Euros at a ticket machine at the airport which took me into the city, getting off at the Universitat exit, in under 30 minutes. I got a map at the Airport tourist information desk and was able to follow the bus route to see where I should get off (combined with information from the hotel website showing where they were from the Universitat metro exit), and from there it's a minute walk. All very easy. In relation to Placa de Catalunya and La Rambla the hotel is less than 5 minutes walk to each, plus there's a tourist information office just another couple minutes walk on La Rambla. My one less than satisfactory issue was that they advertise wi-fi but that appears to only be reliably available in the lobby, from my room I was never able to connect to the hotel signal and intermittently connected to one very weak signal in the area. But that aside I really recommend the convenience, price, ambiance and cleanliness of this hotel. 
